{
  "texts": [
    "The plan and waypoints are then validated Fig. 4 Illustration of transitions in strategies for acquiring model capabilities by a set of environment checks, such as collision detection and inverse kinematics.",
    "If any of the checks fail, the feedback is appended to each agent's prompt and another round of dialog begins.",
    "The agents use LLMs to discuss and improve their plan and waypoints until they pass all validations.",
    "In PREFER [90], the agent first evaluates its performance on a subset of data.",
    "If it fails to solve certain examples, LLMs are leveraged to generate feedback information reflecting on the reasons of the failure."
  ]
}